Jun 8 2009 	Great location that's about it.	Let me say we got a great deal for a King suite at 166 a night, with a restaurant credit. The location is unbeatable. There are great cafes and bars all around. Check in was easy, and the staff was great. I requested a room on a higher floor, and had to wait until about 4 to get in. The room was nice, very modern looking. The beds are a nightmare. I think Europeans, like my husband, are used to sleeping on VERY firm mattresses, but I am not. The linens included no flat sheet, just a comforter. My husband is used to this, I thought it was a nightmare, as I was always either too hot or cold. The view was nice, with floor to ceiling windows. The lights are on dimmers, and take some fumbling to get them working. The minibar is well stocked.Breakfast in the hotel is subpar, and expensive. Go somewhere else. The restaurant is nice looking, but service stinks, and the food is mediocre at best.Here come the concerning parts. Our second night, my husband's key stopped working, so he stopped at the front desk to get a new one. It was about midnight, and the receptionist was on a personal call, took his key, asked what room number, and just reprogrammed it. She did not ask for his ID, or even his name. He could have found that key on the street!Our room was never cleaned. We arrived on a Thurs. Fri, we left the room at noon, and came back at 7, to a dirty room. We figured we may have missed the cleaning window, so we didn't complain. Sat, we left at 8, and came back at 6, to a dirty room. We called down to complain, and ask for at least some new towels. The irony, the minibar was magically checked and restocked each day. Hmmm.That Sat night, we made it an early night, and around 10:30 pm, someone tried to get in our room, using a key. They knocked, but did not announce who they were. I cannot fathom ANY reason a staff member would be in a guests' room at that hour!Checkout was quick, though they made a mistake with the bill. The hotel is just okay, but with the subpar service, I would never stay again.	
