Feb 2 2009 	great hotel for location	stayed here twice in january. once had a very small room on 12th floor, then a nicer room on 16th. Both rooms were the queen/king sized superior rooms. I assumed the smaller room on the 12th was just a design quirk, but I am sure there other rooms of that size. Also, I had some small issues with a draft coming from outside. But as long as you kept the heat on in the room (which you needed since it's pretty cold in nyc during january) you did not feel it. The service and staff was great. The previous comments about a minimalist feel to the rooms is correct. The bathrooms were very clean and comfortable. But since this is new york city, you need to expect the rooms to be small, but the beds were comfortable and you had some great views. I would recommend staying on higher floors since allen street is a busy one. But there are great restaurants around there and you are a 5-10 minute walk from chinatown, little italy, soho, and close to many subway stops. I booked the rooms at quikbook, so I got great rates. Don't know if I would pay full price for the rooms, but that's more a reflection of my budget. I imagine it will be quite popular in the summer with the outdoor pool and bar. The exercise room was adequate but small.	
