Jan 29 2009 	Great Hotel Great Nieghbourhood	Us 3 girls stayed at the Thompson LES for our second annual shopping trip to NY. Had made a great deal with the Smyth Thompson but as it wasn't opened on time we were offered the same rates here. Rooms - Two shared and I had my own room. Very cool and trendy. The concrete ceiling is a bit ridiculous but after the initial sighting I didn't notice anymore. The wooden floors are a bit cold - could have done with slippers. Loved the decor, the tv, the bathroom and shower - everything really. Had the most fantastic view from my room - ESB, Chrysler Building etc. Staff - young, extremely helpful and friendly. Didn't make me feel like I wasn't cool enough to be there like some places do.Didn't eat in the restaurant but had some drinks in the bar which had a great atmosphere and outdoor terrace. We were too busy to get around to checking the spa etc but will do that the next time. The neighbourhood is the best. Lovely streets full of interesting shops, bars and restaurants and within walking distance of all the places we wanted to be at night. We used the subway to get uptown during the day and it was great just to be able to stroll around this vibrant area at night. Loved Mole - the Mexican across the road from the hotel. Jose made the best margahritas and the food was great too. Sugar next to the hotel was great for a good breakfast with friendly service. We all agreed that we will definitely go back again both to the area and the hotel - if we get a good rate. Hope we do!	
