Sep 11 2008 	Why pay more for (THOMPSON) Les?	Are you kidding? Even though none of it's projected perks are up and running Thompson Les is already dishing out attitude. I had the unfortunate experience of staying in the hotel during fashion week and I will never ever ever do so again. Besides the obvious snobbery the hotel experience in itself is just horrible!The rooms are cold and not properly insulated. You can hear your neighbors and doors slamming on the floor. It's a party hotel that is impossible to actual party in. NOTE: No sex at the LES unless you want a call from downstairs - I had to call it was embarrassing for everyone, and I was not alone. Constructions was happening two floors down and yes, you can hear it. While the raw look of the ceiling is intentional, there is a reason for insulation people...sound, temperature comfort, etc. Will they ever remedy this issue? Each floor has the oddest odor also, perhaps its just new carpet but it smells like vomit. An expensive candle on each floor would be nice. The cleaning service arrives at 8am and will persistently return every 15minutes ---so make sure you put up a do not disturb sign...8am really! Internet connections are an issue and the alarms....dear god the alarms!! I read that the construction of this glass monstrosity was cursed and it makes sense now. Never telling, how many artists and elderly people were evicted for the construction of the cheapest place on earth. When I was an artist living in New York in the 1980's the LES stood for something . . . artist, junkies, musicians, real individuals and characters. The Thompson LES is a sad, sad, reminder that all that was once tragically beautiful has been replaced with a shiny new glass facade. Yet, their attempts to be cool and hip are cheap, trite and well...transparent!Sadly sadly disappointed....back to the Hotel Rivington, 60 Thompson or the Mercer.	
